cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image analysis and uses deep learning techniques to extract the topology of filamentary networks such as retinal vessels and road networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the design of a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and its training, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning techniques for topology extraction also suggests the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves extensive evaluation and comparison with baselines, which suggests the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of iterative methods for topology extraction suggests the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
